The paper deals with algorithms and data structures for solving the weighted matching problem on general graphs, as well as extensions to weighted b-matching and f-factors. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), cs.GT (graph theory), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing). However, given the focus on data structures and algorithms, cs.DS is the most likely category. The other categories are also relevant due to the graph-theoretic nature of the problem and the potential for computational geometry techniques to be used in the algorithms.
